  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM2.10.10">
<l>vāraṇaṅko ḷiṭarkkaṭinta mālai nīla marakatattai maḻaimukilē pōlvāṉ ṟaṉṉai</l>
<l>cīraṇaṅku maṟaiyāḷar niṟainta celvat tirukkōva lūrataṉuḷ kaṇṭē ṉeṉṟu</l>
<l>vāraṇaṅku mulaimaṭavār maṅkai vēntaṉ vāṭkaliya ṉoliyaintu maintum vallār</l>
<l>kāraṇaṅka ḷālulakaṅ kalantaṅ kēttak karanteṅkum parantāṉaik kāṇpar tāmē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master these five-and-five verses of sword[-bearing] Kaliyaṉ,</l>
<l rend="indent">chief of Maṅkai, with ladies whose breasts strain their girdles,</l>
<l>Saying, “I saw in prosperous Tirukkōvalūr,</l>
<l rend="indent">filled with Vedic experts whose excellence is desired,</l>
<l>Māl who removed the distress that the elephant endured, the dark emerald,</l>
<l rend="indent">the one like rain clouds,”</l>
<l>By this means, they will see the one who, [though] being hidden,</l>
<l rend="indent">pervades everywhere so that the world [all] together praises [him] there.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
